"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156352","Home Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>We work closely with the police to support the policing of illegal cannabis cultivation and meet them on a regular basis to discuss this issue. <br><br>We have, for example, recently worked in partnership with the police and Crimestoppers on a ‘scratch and sniff’ cannabis card campaign, which ran for one month earlier this year. This involved distributing cards to the public to <br>inform them about the signs to spot and the specific smell of cannabis when it is growing and encourage them to alert the police to suspicious activity. Hot spot areas were targeted by police forces throughout the UK. We are currently <br>working with the police to asses the effectiveness of the campaign but initial reports suggest that this has led to an increase in police activity and built on the success of last year’s campaign.<br><br>The police also work to improve their knowledge and understanding of the trade through activity-led intelligence gathering.<br><br>As well as working with the police, we work with other partners with an interest in this area, such as energy companies and the property sector, to promote cooperation and the sharing of best practice in tackling cannabis cultivation across the UK.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-11-24T14:53:13.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156352/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156352/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-11-18","Cannabis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent discussions she has had with police forces on steps to tackle cannabis cultivation across the UK.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","214833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156353","Home Office","false","2014-11-21","<p>The number of Syrian nationals transferred to Bulgaria, Greece and Italy under the Dublin Convention and the later Dublin II Regulations, because those States are responsible for examining their asylum claims, is shown in the <br>table below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Bulgaria</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Greece</strong></p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Italy</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>*represents a figure below 5.<br><br>The figures quoted have been derived from management information and are therefore provisional and subject to change. This information has not been quality assured under National Statistics protocols.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-11-21T14:36:54.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156353/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156353/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-11-18","Asylum: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Syrian nationals have been returned under the Dublin Regulation to (a) Bulgaria, (b) Italy and (c) Greece in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sarah Teather","Brent Central","Sarah Teather","214846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156354","Home Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>Capacity of the detention estate is kept under rolling review. Decisions will continue to be made according to operational priorities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-11-24T15:10:35.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156354/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156354/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156354/answer/previousversion/29220","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156354/answer/previousversion/29220","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-11-18","Detention Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will halt any expansion of the immigration detention estate until the report from the inquiry by the All-Party Parliamentary Group on Refugees and the All-Party Parliamentary Group on Migration has been published.","false","Biography information for Sarah Teather","Brent Central","Sarah Teather","214847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156355","Home Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>In 2013/14 the total cost of running the Immigration Detention Estate was £164.4m. This includes all costs, including running costs, rent, depreciation and other costs, for all Immigration Removal Centres, Short Term Holding Facilities <br>and amounts paid for spaces in the main prisons estate.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-11-24T15:05:34.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156355/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156355/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156355/answer/previousversion/29221","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156355/answer/previousversion/29221","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-11-18","Detention Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the annual running costs of the immigration detention estate are.","false","Biography information for Sarah Teather","Brent Central","Sarah Teather","214848"
