"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156422","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-25","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and can only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-11-25T15:11:27.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156422/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156422/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156422/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether any (a) external contractors and (b) consultancy companies engaged by his Department have charged more than the initial price agreed for their services since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","214992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156423","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-21","<p>The adoption of this measure is an existing obligation under 1071/2009. The effect for the UK will be low as existing monitoring of operators by the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) already takes into account frequency of minor offences when recommending if the competent authority should commence an action regarding the repute of an operator. The UK is content with the regulation but has questioned the practicality of the implementation date of January 2016.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-11-21T12:06:42.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156423/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156423/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156423/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Transport: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the European Commission's draft Regulation supplementing Regulation (EC) No 1071/2009 with regard to the classification of serious infringements of the Union rules, which may lead to the loss of good repute by the road transport operator; and what his policy is on the proposals in that draft Regulation.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","214970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156424","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-25","<p>We are not aware of any zero emission capable, purpose built taxis in use in London or the rest of the UK. However, a number of zero emission capable, purpose built taxis are planned from a range of manufacturers, and are due for release 2015 onwards. In addition, a small number of zero emission hydrogen taxis were used during the London Olympics. Many private hire vehicle companies across the UK already use zero emission capable vehicles – which are typically hybrid or electric cars, used for commercial purposes.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-11-25T15:05:52.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156424/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156424/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156424/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Taxis: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what comparative assessment he has made of the proportion of taxis in London and the UK that are zero emission capable; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","214861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156425","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-25","<p>The information is not available in this form. However, the attached table (and in the link below) shows the number of buses funded as part of the English Green Bus Fund, including hybrid buses:</p><p /> <p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/344669/green-bus-fund-table.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/344669/green-bus-fund-table.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p /> <p>Details of hybrids in the rest of the UK would be a matter for the relevant devolved administration.</p><p /> <p> </p><p />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-11-25T15:07:27.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156425/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156425/answer","141125 - UIN 214862 - green-bus-fund-table.pdf","141125 - UIN 214862 - green-bus-fund-table.pdf","214862 - English Green Bus Fund Table","214862 - English Green Bus Fund Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156425/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Electric Vehicles: Buses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what comparative assessment he has made of the proportion of buses in London and the UK that are hybrid electric; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","214862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156426","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-24","<p>Forecasts of trip by mode and distance were last published by the Department in Road Transport Forecasts 2011 at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/4243/road-transport-forecasts-2011-results.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/4243/road-transport-forecasts-2011-results.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department has more recently in 2013 produced estimates for the whole of GB using the National Transport Model (NTM). The trip information has not been published but is set out in the tables below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Average Trips per person annually by mode (GB, RTF13 central forecast)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Annual trips</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Walk</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Cycle</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Car Driver</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Car Pgr</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Bus</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Rail</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Total</p><p> </p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>307.4</p></td><td><p>22.1</p></td><td><p>447.6</p></td><td><p>231.8</p></td><td><p>86.3</p></td><td><p>24.4</p></td><td><p>1,119.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2020</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>302.4</p></td><td><p>21.1</p></td><td><p>465.3</p></td><td><p>225.8</p></td><td><p>80.0</p></td><td><p>23.7</p></td><td><p>1,118.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2025</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>298.0</p></td><td><p>20.1</p></td><td><p>483.8</p></td><td><p>219.0</p></td><td><p>73.3</p></td><td><p>22.9</p></td><td><p>1,117.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2030</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>295.7</p></td><td><p>19.9</p></td><td><p>491.6</p></td><td><p>214.0</p></td><td><p>71.2</p></td><td><p>23.4</p></td><td><p>1,115.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2035</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>291.4</p></td><td><p>20.5</p></td><td><p>500.8</p></td><td><p>212.4</p></td><td><p>66.4</p></td><td><p>23.1</p></td><td><p>1,114.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2040</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>290.2</p></td><td><p>20.5</p></td><td><p>507.0</p></td><td><p>211.8</p></td><td><p>64.0</p></td><td><p>23.7</p></td><td><p>1,117.2</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Average length of trips by mode (GB, RTF13 central forecast)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>miles</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Walk</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Cycle</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Car Driver</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Car Pgr</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Bus</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Rail</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>Total</p><p> </p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.5</p></td><td><p>9.0</p></td><td><p>9.9</p></td><td><p>7.8</p></td><td><p>24.7</p></td><td><p>7.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2020</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.4</p></td><td><p>9.1</p></td><td><p>10.0</p></td><td><p>7.9</p></td><td><p>24.7</p></td><td><p>7.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2025</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.3</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.1</p></td><td><p>24.6</p></td><td><p>7.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2030</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.3</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.0</p></td><td><p>24.7</p></td><td><p>7.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2035</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.2</p></td><td><p>24.7</p></td><td><p>7.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2040</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>0.8</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>9.2</p></td><td><p>10.1</p></td><td><p>8.5</p></td><td><p>24.8</p></td><td><p>7.4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Notes on the tables:</p><p> </p><ul><li>These are for personal trips based on main mode of travel. The NTM does not produce mode information for different stages of the same trip.</li><li>These forecasts are based on the central forecast in the Road Traffic Forecasts 2013 (see <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-transport-forecasts-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/road-transport-forecasts-2013</a>. NTM forecasts of trips by mode for the high and low demand scenarios have not been produced.</li><li>The NTM Road Traffic Forecasts should not be viewed as what we think will actually happen in the future, or what we want the future to look like. They are based on our understanding of the way people make travel choices, the expected path of the key drivers at the time the forecast is made and assume no change in government policy beyond that already announced.</li><li>The forecasts do not account for the Departments Cycling Delivery Plan, as this is still in development.</li><li>The NTM is not the Department’s primary forecasting tool for Rail. Therefore the forecasts may not match with Rail forecasts the Department has published elsewhere.</li></ul><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-11-24T12:03:44.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156426/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156426/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156426/answer","Scarborough and Whitby","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156426/answer/previousversion/29296","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156426/answer/previousversion/29296","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what predictions are made by the National Transport Model from 2015 onwards for the (a) average number of trips and stages made annually per person in England and (b) average length of trips by transport mode in the (i) low, (ii) medium and (iii) high growth scenarios.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Huppert","Cambridge","Dr Julian Huppert","214853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156427","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-21","<p>The Department receives funding from Her Majesty’s Treasury for the collection of vehicle excise duty. As abolishing the tax disc has led to a reduction in administration costs, the funding received has been reduced.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-11-21T11:59:57.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156427/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156427/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the savings to the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency generated by the abolition of the tax disc will be returned to the Treasury.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","214856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156428","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-25","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) has safeguards in place to ensure that the release of information to private parking management companies is fair and lawful. These arrangements are kept under constant review.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-11-25T15:09:03.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156428/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156428/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","ParkingEye","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will review the data sharing arrangements between the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency and Parking Eye.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","214889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156429","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-26","<p>The enforcement of cycling offences is an operational matter for individual chief officers of police. Depending on the offence officers can issue verbal warnings, fixed penalty notices or report the road user for formal prosecution. We support any action taken by the police to deter and reduce the number of cycling offences.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-11-26T16:14:50.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156429/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156429/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Road Traffic Offences: Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to reduce the number of pedal cyclists ignoring traffic lights and committing other road offences; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","214935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156430","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-21","<p>The number of individual visits to the Transport Direct Portal for each of the last 5 years was:</p><p>2010 – 20,006,225</p><p>2011 – 21,895,718</p><p>2012 – 21,823,246</p><p>2013 – 21,475,200</p><p>2014 – 14,848,951(Jan to Sept when it was closed down)</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-11-21T12:13:41.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156430/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156430/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156430/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Transport Direct","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many individual visits there were to the Transport Direct website in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","215077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156431","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-21","<p>All customer facing rail staff and managers are required to receive disability awareness training relevant to all disabilities. It is for the industry to decide on the detailed content of the syllabus, but an overview of this training should be submitted to the Office of Rail Regulation annually. We will also intend to commission research on developing good practice guidance on disability awareness training for rail, taxi and bus staff which will address all disabilities, particularly cognitive impairments such as autism.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-11-21T12:10:17.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156431/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156431/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Railways: Learning Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what provision is made for rail passengers under the Think Autism strategy; what steps he has taken to raise awareness of the needs of rail passengers with learning and developmental disabilities; and what recent discussions he has held with train operating companies and Network Rail about the structure and effectiveness of their disability awareness training courses.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","215088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156432","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-21","<p>There is no requirement for a person using a mobility scooter without a number plate to pay vehicle excise duty.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-11-21T11:56:29.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156432/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156432/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-18","Invalid Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether a person using a mobility scooter without a number plate is required to pay vehicle excise duty.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","215079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156433","Wales Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>All aspects of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership were discussed at the Joint Ministerial Committee (Europe) on 13 October 2014, which the Welsh Government Minister for Finance attended.</p><p> </p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb","214881","2014-11-24T11:41:59.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156433/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156433/answer",,,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-11-18","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what representations he has received from the Welsh Government on negotiations on the proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","214883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156434","Wales Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>All aspects of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership were discussed at the Joint Ministerial Committee (Europe) on 13 October 2014, which the Welsh Government Minister for Finance attended.</p><p> </p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb","214883","2014-11-24T11:41:59.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156434/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156434/answer",,,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-11-18","Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what representations he has received from the Welsh Government on exemption of the Welsh National Health Service from negotiations on the proposed Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","214881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156435","Wales Office","false","2014-11-24","<p>No external contractors or consultancy companies engaged by the Wales Office since May 2010 have charged more than the initial price agreed for their services.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2014-11-24T11:43:12.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156435/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156435/answer",,,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-11-18","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, whether any (a) external contractors and (b) consultancy companies engaged by his Department have charged more than the initial price agreed for their services since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","214993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156436","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-24","<p /> <p>DWP engages external contractors through a Crown Commercial Service neutral vendor contract. Each contractor is engaged for a set period and at an agreed daily rate. If it is necessary to extend the period of engagement then a new work order is put in place.</p><p> </p><p>DWP pays consultancy companies on either a fixed price or a time and materials basis as agreed in the contract. A purchase order is put in place for the contract and DWP’s financial systems do not allow for overpayment against the purchase order. Where further work is required over and above that initially agreed then a variation to the contract and purchase order is put in place.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-11-24T12:03:47.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156436/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156436/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-18","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether any (a) external contractors and (b) consultancy companies engaged by his Department have charged more than the initial price agreed for their services since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Chris Evans","Islwyn","Chris Evans","214994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156437","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-21","<p>All customers contacting Access to Work by telephone call a contact centre initially; details of their enquiry are taken and passed to the relevant team to arrange a call back. This applies to general enquiries and payment enquiries. The exception is when a customer has an application awaiting a decision; in these circumstances they will be provided with a name and direct contact number for an adviser.<strong> </strong></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-11-21T12:03:44.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156437/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156437/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-18","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether claimants are able to telephone Access to Work programme offices (a) in general and (b) to discuss late payment of monthly wages for their support workers.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","215028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156438","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-21","<p /> <p>Customers can contact Access to Work by the following means:</p><p>Telephone: 0345/0845 268 8489;</p><p>E-mail: <a href="mailto:atwosu.london@jobcentreplus.gsi.gov.uk" target="_blank">atwosu.london@jobcentreplus.gsi.gov.uk</a>; or</p><p>Textphone: 0345 608 8753</p><p>If a customer is unable to access any of the above communication options, they can appoint a third party to act on their behalf.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-11-21T12:14:32.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156438/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156438/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-18","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what communication options are offered for claimants to contact Access to Work programme offices.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","215029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156439","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-21","<p>Access to Work do not hold any assured data to enable an answer to this question.<strong> </strong></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-11-21T12:08:35.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156439/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156439/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-18","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average time taken by a local Access to Work office to process monthly claims from registered disabled persons for wages for their support workers was over the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","215030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156440","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-25","<p>The information requested is not available as nationality and immigration status of claimants is not currently recorded on benefit payment systems. However the Department has published some general statistics on working age benefit recipients claiming within 6 months of National Insurance Number (NINO) registration. This information is known as “Nationality at point of National Insurance number registration of DWP benefit claimants” and is included in the “Statistical Bulletin on National Insurance Number Allocations to Adult Overseas Nationals Entering the UK – registrations to June 2014”, available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-insurance-number-allocations-to-adult-overseas-nationals-entering-the-uk-to-june-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-insurance-number-allocations-to-adult-overseas-nationals-entering-the-uk-to-june-2014</a></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The Government is looking at ways to reform the current administrative system under Universal Credit so that it will systematically record nationality and immigration status of migrants who make a claim.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-11-25T17:41:56.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156440/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156440/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-18","Social Security Benefits: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the (a) number and (b) proportion of nationals of each EU country who are in the UK and claiming benefits.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","214938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156441","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-21","<p /> <p>The following Work Programme providers have been accredited as ‘Excellent’ under the Merlin Standard since 2012:</p><p> </p><p>Serco - May 2014</p><p>Avanta - May 2014</p><p>G4S - June 2014</p><p>Ingeus - June 2014</p><p>Learn Direct - June 2014</p><p>Maximus - June 2014</p><p>NCG - June 2014</p><p>Reed in Partnership – July 2014</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-11-21T14:35:40.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156441/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156441/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-18","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which Work Programme providers have achieved an excellent accreditation through the Merlin Standards since 2012.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","214912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156442","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-11-21","<p>Current performance measures for DWP include the Off-flow rate, where work is a key destination. Sustained employment is a major focus of Universal Credit, and the Department is currently looking at ways to best reflect that in its performance indicators.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-11-21T14:35:36.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156442/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156442/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-18","Jobcentre Plus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Jobcentre Plus key performance indicators in ensuring jobseekers secure sustainable employment.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","214909"
